The dataset contained daily sales records and no major missing values.
The date column was converted into datetime format and additional features such as year, month, day, and day of week were extracted.
Linear Regression was used for sales forecasting.
Model performance was evaluated using MAE, RMSE, and R² score.
The model was able to generate future sales predictions, but the evaluation metrics indicated that simple linear regression may not fully capture complex sales patterns and seasonality.
Advanced forecasting techniques like ARIMA, SARIMA, or Prophet could improve prediction accuracy.
